  {"id": "94eb800d-s1", "templateId": "words-in-context.A2.T5.medium", "verdict": "type_drift", "detail": "T5 requires the blank to be a verb naming a causal/functional action with directional polarity cue. Here the blank verb 'produced' is just the basic action of creation with no causal mechanism or directional polarity at stake. The stem fits T3 (restatement: 'made' the films) rather than a cause/effect/function cue."},
  {"id": "995358b4-s1", "templateId": "words-in-context.A2.T4.medium", "verdict": "type_drift", "detail": "Tagged T4 (contrast cue) but functions as T5: 'although' introduces context, but the blank itself names the causal action ('destabilized') of heavy nectar inflow on labor balance. No antonym pole is being supplied to contrast a named entity; the blank fills the causal effect verb."},
  {"id": "9aa44886-s1", "templateId": "words-in-context.A1.T1.medium", "verdict": "ok"},
  {"id": "9c35759f-s1", "templateId": "words-in-context.A2.T5.medium", "verdict": "type_drift", "detail": "Stem turns on contrast ('refuses to ___...willingness to upend...avoid predictable'), not on a causal/functional mechanism. Better fits T4 (contrast cue) with negation framing, not T5."},
